Key Match Events: Yankuba Minteh scored in the seventh minute of added time to secure a draw for Gambia in their previous match against Madagascar.
Clement Couturier scored for Madagascar in the second minute of stoppage time at the end of the first half in their previous match against Gambia.
Pre-Game Insights: Gambia went into the previous match as marginal favorites and dominated the game with 22 shots at goal.
Due to stadiums in Gambia not meeting FIFA standards, Gambia is forced to play their 'home' games at a neutral venue in Morocco.
Madagascar has shown improvement under coach Romuald Rakotondrabe, losing only three of their last 10 games.
Minteh has been a key player for Gambia, contributing to three of their last four goals.
